title: DSC209R Project 1: Expository Visualization
description: We are presented with a dataset of over 50,000 food items sold by Walmart, Target, and Whole Foods. These food items contained detailed information, including their degree of processing and nutritional content. The food that is stocked by each of these stores, as well as their price, influences the purchases made by consumers. This concept drove my inspiration and motivation for the takeaway I want my audience to understand: some food items are more accessible than others, in more ways than one.

title: DSC232R Project: Classification of Dermatoscopic Images
description: This is my project for my UCSD DSC232R course, being done in the Spring 2025 quarter. This project deals with images of skin lesions and attempts to accurately classify which images contain malignant skin lesions (i.e. melanoma) and which images contain benign skin lesions (i.e. nevus, seborrheic keratosis). title: DSC207R Final Project: Working with Baseball Data
description: For my final project in DSC207R, I decided to work with baseball data, specifically data from Major League Baseball (MLB). Baseball is a sport that is rich in statistics and data, making it a great candidate for data visualization. My goal for this project was to create visualizations that would help to tell a story about the game of baseball and its players. Project
